FR940214-2-00052 FR940214-2-00037 Determinations Regarding Eligibility To Apply for Worker Adjustment Assistance and NAFTA Transitional Adjustment Assistance In accordance with Section 223 of the Trade Act of 1974, as amended, the Department of Labor herein presents summaries of determinations regarding eligibility to apply for trade adjustment assistance for workers (TA&hyph;W) issued during the period of February, 1994. In order for an affirmative determination to be made and a certification of eligibility to apply for worker adjustment assistance to be issued, each of the group eligibility requirements of Section 222 of the Act must be met. (1) That a significant number or proportion of the workers in the worker's firm, or an appropriate subdivision thereof, have become totally or partially separated, (2) That sales or production, or both, of the firm or subdivision have decreased absolutely, and (3) That increases of imports of articles like or directly competitive with articles produced by the firm or appropriate subdivision have contributed importantly to the separations, or threat thereof, and to the absolute decline in sales or production. Negative Determinations for Worker Adjustment Assistance In each of the following cases the investigation revealed that criterion (3) has not been met. A survey of customers indicated that increased import did not contribute importantly to worker separations at the firm. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,090; McMurry Oil Tools, Inc., Huntsville, TX TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,210; Aluminum Co of America, Lafayette, IN TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,205; Dyna Turn of Oklahoma, Inc., Elk City, OK TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,209; Beaver Precision Products, Troy, MI TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,217; Northrop Electronics Systems Div., Hawthorne, CA TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,326; Rockwell International (NAAD), El Segundo, CA TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,326A; Rockwell Autonetics Electronics Systems, Anaheim, CA In the following cases, the investigation revealed that the criteria for eligibility have not been met for the reasons specified. TA&hyph;W&hyph;28,339; Tuboscope Pipeline Service, Houston, TX The workers' firm does not produce an article as required for certification under Section 222 of the Trade Act of 1974. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,373; Human Resource Technologies, Inc., (HRT), Oklahoma City, OK The workers' firm does not produce an article as required for certification under Section 222 of the Trade Act of 1974. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,335; Restaura, Inc., Wentzville, MO The worker's firm does not produce an article as required for certification under Section 222 of the Trade Act of 1974. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,120; John Roberts/Act II, Inc., Biddeford, MI Increased imports did not contribute importantly to worker separations at the firm. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,216; Synergy Consultants, Inc., Denver, CO The workers' firm does not produce an article as required for certification under Section 222 of the Trade Act of 1974. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,321; Frigidaire Co., Connersville, IN The investigation revealed that criterion (2) has not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period for certification. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,237; Uniroyal Goodrich Tire Co., Woodburn, IN The investigation revealed that criterion (2) has not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period for certification. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,241; Armco Advanced Materials Co., Buttler, PA The investigation revealed that criterion (2) has not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period for certification. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,265; Smith & Wesson, Springfield, MA The investigation revealed that criterion (2) has not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period for certification. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,292; Sandvik Special Metals Corp., Kennewick, WA The investigation revealed that criterion (2) has not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period for certification. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,279, TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,280, TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,281; Champion Int'l Corp, Milltown, MT, Bonner, MT, Libby, MT (Plant) The investigation revealed that criterion (2) has not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period for certification. TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,282, TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,283, TA&hyph;W&hyph;29,284; Champion Int'l Corp, Libby, MT (Office), Missoula, MT (Plant), Missoula, MT (Office) The investigation revealed that criterion (2) has not been met. Sales or production did not decline during the relevant period for certification.
